@startuml PicoGallery – Dynamic: Device Setup Flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #555555
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #888888
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #FFF8E1
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"

title PicoGallery — Device Setup Flow (Dynamic View)

participant "Mobile App" as App
participant "startup.sh" as Boot
participant "provision.py\n:80" as Prov
participant "web_creator.py\n:5678" as WC
participant "bot.py\n:3457" as Bot
participant "cloudflared" as CF
participant "Telegram API" as TG

== First Boot ==

Boot -> Boot : WiFi flag missing?
Boot -> Prov : start (hotspot mode)
note right of Prov
  Pi creates "Helles-Setup" hotspot
  IP: 10.42.0.1
end note

App -> Prov : GET /?mode=app\n(phone on hotspot)
Prov --> App : WiFi form

App -> Prov : POST /save-wifi\n{ssid, password}
Prov -> Prov : nmcli connect + write .wifi_configured
Prov --> App : "WiFi Connecting…" page

Boot -> Boot : .wifi_configured detected\nwait for internet (ping 8.8.8.8)

== Bot Creation ==

Boot -> WC   : systemctl start botcreator\n(wait for TELEGRAM_TOKEN + CHAT_ID in .env)

App -> WC    : GET /?mode=app\n(Bot Setup button)
WC --> App   : phone number form

App -> WC    : POST phone → Telegram code flow
note right of WC
  Full headless BotFather flow:
  1. my.telegram.org API credentials
  2. Create bot via BotFather
  3. Send /start, receive chat_id
end note

WC -> WC     : write TELEGRAM_TOKEN + CHAT_ID\nto Chatbot/.env
WC --> App   : done page ("close this page")

App -> WC    : GET /config
WC --> App   : {"token": "...", "chat_id": "..."}
App -> App   : save to SecureStore (botConfig)

Boot -> Boot : credentials detected → break loop

== Service Start ==

Boot -> Bot  : systemctl start chatbot
Boot -> CF   : systemctl start cloudflared

CF -> CF     : acquire tunnel URL
CF -> CF     : write URL to tunnel.url

Bot -> TG    : sendMessage "✅ bot started"
Bot -> Bot   : read tunnel.url
Bot -> TG    : sendMessage + pinChatMessage\n🔗 https://xxx.trycloudflare.com

== URL Discovery (Local Network) ==

App -> Bot   : GET :3457/url
Bot --> App  : {"url": "https://xxx.trycloudflare.com"}
App -> App   : setServer(url) → login screen

== URL Discovery (Remote / Mobile Data) ==

App -> App   : discoverPiHost() → all fail\n(Pi not on same network)
App -> TG    : getChat?chat_id=...\n(using stored botConfig)
TG --> App   : pinned_message.text\n"🔗 https://xxx.trycloudflare.com"
App -> App   : extract URL via regex\nsetServer(url) → login screen

== Tunnel URL Change ==

CF -> CF     : tunnel restarts → new URL
CF -> CF     : overwrite tunnel.url
Bot -> Bot   : watcher detects change (every 10 s)
Bot -> TG    : sendMessage + pinChatMessage\n🔗 https://yyy.trycloudflare.com

note right of Bot
  App will pick up the new URL
  on next "Connect to Server"
  via local :3457/url or Telegram pin
end note

@enduml
